Implementation details for CloudWatch Logs, input validation, and ECR cleanup:

## CloudWatch Logs Integration (spec compliance fix)
- Spec: aws-provider.md line 60 - 'Set up CloudWatch logging'
- provisionLogGroup(): Creates /ecs/agent-deploy-{infraID} log group
- Retention policy: 7 days (balances debuggability vs cost)
- createTaskDefinition(): Adds LogConfiguration with awslogs driver
- deleteLogGroup(): Cleanup during teardown

## Input Validation (robustness fix)
- planInfra now validates all required inputs before processing
- Catches empty/whitespace strings for app_description and region
- Catches non-positive integers for expected_users and latency_ms
- Error messages identify which field failed validation

## ECR Repository Cleanup (cost management)
- deleteECRRepository(): Added to teardown sequence
- Uses force=true to delete repository even with images
- Prevents storage cost accumulation from orphaned repos

## Testing
- 7 new test cases in TestPlanInfra_InputValidation
- Tests cover all validation scenarios (empty, whitespace, zero, negative)

## Dependencies
- Added github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/cloudwatchlogs v1.64.1

## Why These Changes Matter
1. CloudWatch Logs: Essential for debugging deployed applications
2. Input validation: Prevents invalid plans from being created
3. ECR cleanup: Prevents cost leaks from orphaned repositories
